  "texts": [
    "Respiratory Motion Compensation1) Surrogate Signal: An EM sensor was implemented to track the displacement of the liver phantom.",
    "The detected displacements in the y-and z-axes of the sensor served as a surrogate signal.",
    "In [24] and [25], it was observed that EM trackers can be used in human subjects as surrogate signals when attached to the abdominal area.",
    "In this work, the sensor was attached externally to the liver phantom.",
    "The obtained motion simulates the external abdominal skin motion during respiration.2) Ground Truth: The ground truth represents the actual motion of the target."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "In [24] and [25], it was observed that EM trackers can be used in human subjects as surrogate signals when attached to the abdominal area."
  ]
